## ⚠️ PRODUCT ANTI-PATTERNS

### Never Do This
```yaml
Feature Creep:
  - Adding without value
  - Complexity for sake of it
  - Ignoring user needs
  - Feature over stability

Bad Prioritization:
  - Tech desires over user needs
  - New over fixing
  - Complex over simple
  - Perfect over shipped

Quality Compromise:
  - Accepting mocks
  - Ignoring performance
  - Skipping crisis scenarios
  - No pattern extraction
```

